This paper is about using deep neural networks to learn to play the chess variant Crazyhouse. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses modifications in the neural network design and training configuration, which could fall under the sub-category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions Monte-Carlo tree search, which is a common technique in Game Theory (cs.GT) and Reinforcement Learning (cs.NE). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, followed by cs.GT, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
